{
  "doc_id": "4201",
  "text": "Our findings suggest that early initiation of galsulfase ERT is important to maximize growth potential. The finding of an age-dependent benefit of galsulfase ERT is consistent with previous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . In particular, sibling studies in which one sibling begins therapy at a much younger age than the other provide compelling evidence of benefits of early galsulfase ERT initiation [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Additionally, a 2-year Brazilian study of MPS VI children undergoing galsulfase ERT starting at 3 years of age showed that 15 of 32 (47%) patients maintained or increased their pre-treatment growth percentile (per World Health Organization reference charts) relative to unaffected individuals [CITATION_7] . Whether the greater height gain also results in reduced morbidity and increased survival [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] is an important topic for future investigation.",
